                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>No American record of this conversation has been found. According to the account
                    in Pickersgill, p. 513, from which the information set forth above has been
                    derived, Roosevelt told Mackenzie King that he had sent a message to Stalin
                    asking for a bilateral meeting. Roosevelt was concerned about Churchill’s
                    possible reaction to the proposal. For text of Roosevelt’s May 5, 1943, message
                    to Stalin, see <ref target="frus1943CairoTehran#pg_3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, The Conferences at Cairo and
                        Tehran, 1943, p. 3</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
